-- Coffee Output May Drop in Karnataka, India's Biggest Grower, Times Says
-- B y   T h o m a s   A b r a h a m
-- 2010-11-09T01:32:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-11-09/coffee-output-may-drop-in-india-s-biggest-grower-on-rains-times-reports.html
Coffee production in Karnataka,
India’s biggest grower, may drop this year because of excess
rainfall, the Economic Times reported, citing an official at a
grower’s group. Arabica bean output may drop 20 percent and
robusta coffee may be lower by 10 percent, B. Subramani,
president of Kodagu Coffee Growers Cooperative Society, told the
newspaper.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Thomas Abraham in Mumbai at 
